chart_description: This chart shows the percentage distribution of latencies for Data Encryption Key(DEK) Generation Operations in Kubernetes API Server. These latencies indicate the time taken by the API server to generate a new DEK for storing secrets in etcd datastore. Higher percentage values in a specific latency range may indicate potential bottlenecks or performance issues in API server - etcd communication or etcd storage.

dimension_descriptions.+Inf: The percentage of operations that took longer than the maximum measured latency.
dimension_descriptions.10 \u00b5s: The percentage of operations that took less than 10 microseconds.
dimension_descriptions.20 \u00b5s: The percentage of operations that took between 10 and 20 microseconds.
dimension_descriptions.40 \u00b5s: The percentage of operations that took between 20 and 40 microseconds.
dimension_descriptions.80 \u00b5s: The percentage of operations that took between 40 and 80 microseconds.
dimension_descriptions.160 \u00b5s: The percentage of operations that took between 80 and 160 microseconds.
dimension_descriptions.320 \u00b5s: The percentage of operations that took between 160 and 320 microseconds.
dimension_descriptions.640 \u00b5s: The percentage of operations that took between 320 and 640 microseconds.
dimension_descriptions.1280 \u00b5s: The percentage of operations that took between 640 and 1280 microseconds.
dimension_descriptions.2560 \u00b5s: The percentage of operations that took between 1280 and 2560 microseconds.
dimension_descriptions.5120 \u00b5s: The percentage of operations that took between 2560 and 5120 microseconds.
dimension_descriptions.10240 \u00b5s: The percentage of operations that took between 5120 and 10240 microseconds.
dimension_descriptions.20480 \u00b5s: The percentage of operations that took between 10240 and 20480 microseconds.
dimension_descriptions.40960 \u00b5s: The percentage of operations that took between 20480 and 40960 microseconds.
